      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">詩經·小雅·鹿鳴之什·001.1</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">鹿鳴.1</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>呦呦鹿鳴，食野之苹。我有嘉賓，鼓瑟吹笙。
吹笙鼓簧，承筐是將。人之好我，示我周行。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>With pleased sounds the deer call to one another,
Eating the celery of the fields.
I have here admirable guests;
The lutes are struck, and the organ is blown for them; --
The organ is blown till its tongues are all moving.
The baskets of offerings also are presented to them.
The men love me,
And will show me the perfect path.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="shijing__xiaoya-luming-001__002__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr">
      <prop type="x-work-id">shijing</prop>
